title.narrative: Operational support for delivery of programme results

description.narrative: During 2021, the country office Supply Unit supported programmes to procure goods and services, including supplies for emergencies, with a total value of more than US$ 2.8 million. As a coordinator/facilitator/intermediary for COVID-19 response, UNICEF contributed to ensuring the successful delivery of over $ 38.4 million worth of COVID-19 vaccines and more than $ 2.6 million worth of syringes. UNICEF supported the government with cold chain equipment ($ 3.8 million) to ensure quality vaccines reached targeted destinations nationwide. | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/02/2022
